# Backend environment (local tools: Alembic, pytest, IDE)

Copy to `backend/.env` when running the API **outside** Docker against a local or remote DB.

For **Docker Compose**, use the **repository root** `.env` (see root `.env.example`); Compose injects `DATABASE_URL` for the backend service.

# Plain ``postgres://`` / ``postgresql://`` (e.g. Render ``DATABASE_URL``) is normalized to ``+asyncpg`` in code.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://kff:kff@localhost:5432/kff
SECRET_KEY=change-me-to-a-long-random-string
CORS_ORIGINS=["http://localhost:8081","http://localhost:3000","http://localhost:5173","http://localhost:8080"]

# Post images: leave unset for local uvicorn (repo ``../data`` is auto-detected). Docker Compose sets ``MEDIA_PUBLIC_ROOT=/media`` and mounts ``./data`` read-write at ``/media/data``.

# STORAGE_BACKEND=local
# S3_BUCKET=
# S3_REGION=
# BLIP_DISABLE=false
# Optional: persist Hugging Face downloads when running uvicorn locally (default: ~/.cache/huggingface).
# HF_HOME=/absolute/path/to/hf-cache

USDA_API_KEY=

# Anthropic API key for AI-assisted EN→ES translation in the admin panel.
# Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com — leave blank to disable the feature.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
